steps.text:
VS Code now supports the preferred visual-line behavior by default: adding cursors above/below follows wrapped screen lines.

To explicitly bind it:

```json
{
  "key": "ctrl+alt+down",
  "command": "editor.action.insertCursorBelow",
  "args": { "logicalLine": false }
}
```

Use `"logicalLine": true` if you instead want cursors added only on the next actual (unwrapped) document line.
